Latin America, and the Middle East. This groundbreaking study of China’s “soft power” initiatives in these countries offers, for the first time, the diverse perspectives of scholars and diplomats from Oceania, North American, China, and Japan. It explores such issues as regional competition for diplomatic and economic ties between Taiwan and China, the role of overseas Chinese in developing these relationships, and various analyses of the benefits and drawbacks of China’s growing presence in Oceania. In addition, the reader obtains a rare review of the Japanese response to China’s role in Oceania, presented by Japan’s leading scholar of the Pacific region.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aIati, Iati, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIzumi, Kobayashi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKabutaulaka, Tarcisius Tara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLanga‘oi, Palenitina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMita, Takashi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNelson, Hank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPorter, Edgar A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPorter, Edgar A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPowles, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTarte, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWesley-Smith, Terence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWesley-Smith, Terence, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWillmott, Bill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 a